  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Your Word Counts - Improved Feedback Mechanisms</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project represents the Partner Affiliate (PA) contribution component of the Your Word Counts project. A grant will be given to fund work in Occupied Palestinian Territory and Israel (OPTI) to support programme staff to have improved skills and knowledge of feedback within their programmes and to be able to make changes and influence decision makers to respond to feedback more effectively. This will help deliver high quality programmes that use Information and Communication Techniques  (ICTs) for their collection, management and reporting on feedback received from communities.   The Your Word Counts project is committed to capturing learning and knowledge about ICT good practice. Regular check ins and adaptations will take place based on feedback from country teams. The methodology and the technology will be flexible to incorporate the knowledge and learning from each country. A yearly learning event will also seek to bring the country Monitoring Evaluation and Accountability and Learning (MEAL) staff together to share learning and discuss success and failures as well as improvements. Bi -monthly blogs will be written by one of the project team, as per donor requirements and all documentation will be published and promoted through Policy and Practice.</narrative>
  </description>
